14/01/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- A Turkish court on Thursday (13 January) sentenced a Hizbullah militant to life in prison for the killing of a police chief and five officers in Diyarbakir in January 2001. 
Mehmet Fidanci was one of 15 Islamic militants who were charged with carrying out the attack. 
The others trials continue.
In other news, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said he wants to meet UN Secretary General Kofi Annan as soon as possible for talks on the reunification of Cyprus. 
He announced that his government would support any new initiative that would benefit both parts of the divided island. 
(AFP - 13/01/05)
